places.name: Bahá'í House of Worship
places.perex: The Bahá'í Faith in Samoa and American Samoa begins with the then head of the religion, `Abdu'l-Bahá, mentioning the islands in 1916.

places.name: Lepuia'i
places.perex: Lepuia'i is one of four small villages on Manono Island in Samoa. The village population is 223.

places.name: Monte Silisili
places.perex: El monte Silisili es el pico más alto de Samoa. Está situado en el centro de la isla de Savai'i y se eleva a una altura de el 1858 metros.

Aeropuerto Internacional Faleolo
places.perex: El Aeropuerto Internacional Faleolo es el aeropuerto internacional de Samoa.

places.name: Asau Airport
places.perex: Asau Airport is a small domestic airfield located in the thick dense jungle at the northwest end of Savai'i in Samoa.

places.name: Maota Airport
places.perex: Maota Airport is the main domestic airport on the island of Savai'i in Samoa. It is situated near Salelologa at the east end of Savai'i.
